               <head>Jamiʻ al-qavanin</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of Jāmi‘ al-qavānīn by Qanawjī, Khalīfah Shāh Muḥammad, active 17th century</summary>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85076229 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85100074" n="1" xml:id="Uk_Or_15662-item1">
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" type="supplied" key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164656430.0x000001 viaf_178125018">Qanawjī, Khalīfah Shāh Muḥammad, active 17th century</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="per" key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164656430.0x000001 viaf_178125018" type="supplied">قنوجى، خلیفه شاه محمد</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_8186">Jāmi‘ al-qavānīn</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_8186">جامع القوانین</title>
                     <note>
                        <p>Collected ornate letters (inshāʾ), also called <title>Inshā-yi Khalīfah</title>, by Khalīfah Shāh Muḥammad. Written while the author was studying at Qannauj, northern India (preface, f. 2r), the work was completed in 1055/1645-6. 
                        </p>
                        <p>Comprises four faṣls and a khātimah. </p>
                        <p>Other contents: front inside cover and endpaper, descriptions by former owners (including: ‘M.S. Persan no. 8, Loix, préceptes et formules’), and bookplate of Le Ch. Ferrao de Castelbranco. </p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per">Persian</textLang>
                     <filiation/>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
